content.description:
Start by face climbing and jamming up a short hand crack with excellent jams and holds.

From the ledge move behind the pillars to where you can exit to the cliff top. There may be no/minimal pro on this section.
content.location: Middle of the green wall. Look for a short hand crack ending on a ledge 15 feet or so off the ground

content.description: Ascends a double crack with loose rock on route and especially near the top. Probably best for belayer to be off to the side. Chain anchor on top.
content.location: Located on the right end of the Green Wall (see pictures).

content.description: Climb wide crack to mesa top.
content.protection:
Gear to 7".

3"-4" gear may be useful to build a belay.
content.location:
4 cracks right of hand jive.

Look for the right facing OW.

content.description: Climb double cracks to a hand crack ending at a chain anchor.
content.location:
Far right side of the green wall.

Look for the hand crack with a chain anchor.

content.description: Climb offwidth and loose face to chain anchor.
content.location:
East facing side of the

Green Wall

, north end.

Around the corner from

Gerbil Lies

look for an offwidth.

content.description: Climb thin hand crack to a small ledge. Climb bulge with a handcrack to mesa top.
content.protection:
Single rack to 3 inches

Belay from bolts up top and left.
content.location: Hand crack right of the corner, Gerbil Lies.

content.description: Climb the clean hand crack which features many large face holds.
content.protection:
Gear to 3.5 Inches. Mostly in the 1"-3" range.

Belay bolts are on top. These bolts do not have chains. These bolts are not visible from below.
content.location: The corner hand crack that is the first route around the corner from the zig-zag wall side.
